---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Option C — Shibaura" activeTab="shibaura">
  <div class="mb-8">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="tier-badge bg-shibaura/20 text-shibaura text-sm">C — Safer</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold">Shibaura Institute of Technology</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mt-2">Innovative Global Program (IGP) — Mechanical Engineering major</p>
  </div>

  <blockquote>
    Engineering-specialist institute in Tokyo with a small English-taught IGP explicitly designed for international high-school graduates. OCSI's ACSI accreditation is directly accepted. Sept 2028 entry, 3-month gap. Tuition ~&yen;1.65M/year. Lower SAT bar than Waseda but <strong>very small cohort (9 students/year)</strong>.
  </blockquote>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>The university</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Shibaura Institute of Technology (SIT)</strong> is a Tokyo-based engineering-specialist university with strong ties to Japanese industry. Not a top-prestige name like Waseda or Todai, but a serious engineering institution with consistently good employment outcomes. Classified as one of MEXT's "Super Global Universities" with explicit funding to internationalise.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>The program</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Innovative Global Program (IGP)</strong> — a fully English-taught Bachelor of Engineering with six selectable majors.
      Ivan would choose <strong>Mechanical Engineering</strong>.
    </p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Detail</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Cohort size</td><td><strong>9 students/year</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Language</td><td>100% English instruction</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Length</td><td>4 years</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Intakes</td><td>Spring (April) and Fall (September) — target <strong>Fall 2028</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Majors</td><td>Mechanical, Applied Chemistry, CS, Electronics, Materials, Engineering Education</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Research</td><td>From year 1</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Accreditation</td><td>OCSI's <strong>ACSI</strong> is explicitly listed as acceptable</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Pros and cons</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="card border-green-900/40">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-green-400 text-base">Pros</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> <strong>Designed for international students</strong> from US-style schools</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> <strong>Lower SAT bar</strong> than Waseda — focus on in-house exam</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Engineering-focused environment from day 1</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Similar cost to Waseda but less competitive</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Mechanical Engineering is a named major</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Strong industry placement track</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> MEXT University Recommendation — small program = better odds</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card border-red-900/40">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-red-400 text-base">Cons</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> <strong>Tiny cohort (9/year)</strong> — unpredictable acceptance</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Lower brand prestige than Waseda outside engineering circles</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> More complex application: docs + presentation + interview + test</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Smaller alumni network</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Less name recognition for grad school abroad</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Tokyo cost of living applies</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Spring intake (April) doesn't fit OCSI — must target Fall</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Admission requirements</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Detail</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Diploma</td><td>12-year accredited education — <strong>ACSI explicitly accepted (OCSI qualifies)</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Prerequisites</td><td>Math + (Physics OR Chemistry) at high school level</td></tr>
          <tr><td>GPA</td><td>No fixed minimum published</td></tr>
          <tr><td>SAT / ACT</td><td><strong>Not required</strong> — IGP runs its own maths and physics entrance test</td></tr>
          <tr><td>English</td><td>TOEFL iBT 80+ / IELTS 6.0+ (possible waiver for OCSI)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Japanese / EJU</td><td><strong>Not required</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Application components</td><td>Documents + internet-based test + online interview + maths/physics tests + web presentation</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Platform</td><td>TAO (The Admissions Office)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">
      The IGP admissions process is intentionally <strong>multi-component</strong> — they want to see how Ivan thinks under various conditions, not just one snapshot.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Cost</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">2026 published rates — verify in 2027</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Per year</th><th>4-year total</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Tuition (engineering)</td><td>~&yen;1,600,000 - 1,700,000</td><td>~&yen;6,600,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Admission fee (year 1)</td><td>~&yen;280,000</td><td>~&yen;280,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Living costs in Tokyo</td><td>~&yen;1,500,000 - 1,800,000</td><td>~&yen;6,600,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>National Health Insurance</td><td>~&yen;20,000</td><td>~&yen;80,000</td></tr>
          <tr class="font-bold text-white">
            <td>Approximate 4-year total</td>
            <td></td>
            <td class="text-shibaura">~&yen;13,500,000 (~USD 90,000)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-4">
      <h3 class="mt-0 text-base">Scholarships worth applying for</h3>
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 mb-0">
        <li><strong>SIT IGP merit-based scholarships</strong> — partial tuition reductions</li>
        <li><strong>JASSO Honors Scholarship</strong> — &yen;48,000/month after arrival</li>
        <li><strong>MEXT University Recommendation</strong> — SIT can nominate IGP students directly (small cohort improves odds)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Application timeline</h2>
    <div class="mermaid-container">
      <pre class="mermaid">
gantt
    title  Shibaura IGP — Application Timeline (Sept 2028 entry)
    dateFormat  YYYY-MM-DD
    axisFormat  %b %Y

    section Preparation
    AP Calc AB + AP Physics (G11)     :2026-08-17, 280d
    Begin TAO platform account        :milestone, 2027-06-01, 0d
    Prepare web presentation video    :2027-07-01, 60d
    Maths + Physics drilling          :2027-08-01, 75d
    TOEFL iBT                         :milestone, 2027-08-15, 0d

    section Application (Fall intake)
    Application window OPENS          :milestone, 2027-11-04, 0d
    Submit application                :milestone, 2027-11-10, 0d
    Application window CLOSES         :milestone, 2027-11-18, 0d
    1st screening (document review)   :2027-11-18, 65d
    1st screening results             :milestone, 2028-01-23, 0d

    section Round 2
    Online interview                  :milestone, 2028-02-15, 0d
    Maths + physics test (online)     :milestone, 2028-02-15, 0d
    Final decision                    :milestone, 2028-03-26, 0d

    section Enrolment
    Accept offer + deposit            :milestone, 2028-04-15, 0d
    OCSI graduation                   :milestone, 2028-05-26, 0d
    Status of Residence transfer      :2028-05-01, 90d
    Tokyo accommodation               :2028-06-01, 90d
    Semester begins                   :milestone, 2028-09-25, 0d
      </pre>
    </div>

    <h3>Key dates</h3>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Sep 2026</td><td>Lock in AP Calc + AP Physics for Grade 11</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Jun 2027</td><td>Create TAO platform account</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Jul-Aug 2027</td><td>Prepare web presentation video (script + record + edit)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Aug 2027</td><td>TOEFL iBT</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Aug-Oct 2027</td><td>Drill maths and physics for entrance test</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Nov 4, 2027</td><td>Application window opens</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">~Nov 10, 2027</td><td>Submit application</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Nov 18, 2027</td><td>Application window closes</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">~Jan 23, 2028</td><td>1st screening results</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">~Feb 15, 2028</td><td>Round 2: interview + maths/physics test</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">~Mar 26, 2028</td><td>Final decision</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Apr 15, 2028</td><td>Accept offer + deposit</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">~Sep 25, 2028</td><td>Semester begins</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Application checklist</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>Create TAO platform account by June 2027</li>
      <li>Take TOEFL iBT — target 80+ (95+ helps)</li>
      <li>AP scores: Calculus + Physics, both 4+</li>
      <li>Web-based presentation: 3-5 minute video (introduce yourself, motivation, project example)</li>
      <li>Document portfolio: transcript, recommendation, statement</li>
      <li>Prepare for maths/physics entrance test (AP Calc + AP Physics curriculum)</li>
      <li>Prepare for online interview (English under pressure on technical topics)</li>
      <li>Submit application via TAO, Nov 4-18, 2027</li>
      <li>Application fee: &yen;35,000</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Russian passport — practical notes</h2>
    <div class="card border-surface-600">
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
        <li>Same as Waseda: <strong>zero issues</strong>.</li>
        <li>Ivan is already a Japan resident. Status of Residence transfer is routine and SIT's international office handles it.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Realistic verdict</h2>
    <div class="card border-shibaura/30">
      <p class="mb-3">Shibaura IGP is a <strong>legitimate safer option but not a trivial one</strong>. Two things make it the right Option C:</p>
      <ol class="text-sm space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li><strong>OCSI's accreditation is directly listed as acceptable</strong> — minimal administrative friction.</li>
        <li><strong>No SAT requirement</strong> — if Ivan's SAT comes in below the Waseda bar (1450+), Shibaura is still in reach.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="bg-shibaura/10 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-shibaura font-semibold mb-1">Strategy</p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-0">
          Apply in <strong>November 2027</strong>, before either Melbourne or Waseda decisions arrive.
          If accepted in March 2028, Ivan has a confirmed Japan-based engineering placement with the option to upgrade
          if Waseda or Melbourne come through later. This sequencing is the entire reason Shibaura exists in the plan — early decision, anchor option, low downside.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
